item.title: Of Musk and Afroman
item.description:
An Elon Musk-worshipping college principal gets schooled, and rapper Afroman turns the tables after armed police raid his house.

All this and much more is discussed in the latest edition of the "Smashing Security" podcast by computer security veterans Graham Cluley and Carole Theriault.

Warning: This podcast may contain nuts, adult themes, and rude language.

Episode links:

  • These Men's Rights Activists Literally Worship Elon Musk - Buzzfeed News... Feed: https://feeds.captivate.fm/smashing-security/

item.title: Ep #323 From a Childhood in Poverty to 300 Million in Sales Interview With Matthew Gallagher Founder and CEO Watch Gang
item.description:
I got to speak to Matthew Gallagher.


Matthew is Los Angeles based entrepreneur with a history in computer engineering and digital advertising. As the founder and CEO of Watch Gang, Matthew oversees the day to day business operations of the world's largest watch club, leading the business to $300M in sales. Matthew's childhood in poverty made him passionate about helping others and led him to becoming a committed philanthropist... Feed: https://anchor.fm/s/17ba6a0/podcast/rss
